SIEM is used to correlate the data collected to detect threats. It gives a warning when a threat is detected or when a particular threshold is exceeded. This warning enables analysts to take quantity -based measures. It provides good visibility as to what is over in the network infrastructure.

Siem skills

=> Correlation between events from different daily resources.
=> visibility is achieved in both host -based and network -centered activities.
=> Gives a trace of analysts' latest threats and timely response research.
=> Investigates threats that cannot be determined by the rules in force.

SOC analyst responsibilities
SOC analysts use Siem solutions to better use what is going on in the network.

::: Monitoring and research
::: Determining the wrong positive
::: adjustment rules that cause noise or wrong positive
::: Reporting and compatibility
::: Bringing the blind spots in network visibility and closing them